text:
Merge pull request #303 from mbdevpl/pkg_resources_fix

added 3 pkg_resources functions to brain
issues: [{u'raw': u'#303', u'refstyle': u'#d', u'parts': [u'pycqa', u'astroid', u'303', u'']}]

text: Propagate error information to @raise_if_nothing_inferred in unpack_infer()

Fix unpack_infer to fail if results are empty

This should prevent a StopIteration leaking when next is called
over unpack_infer.

added 3 pkg_resources functions to brain

[Those 3 are] methods of WorkingSet objects [that] are also available
as module- level functions in pkg_resources that apply to the default
working_set instance. Thus, you can use e.g. pkg_resources.require()
as an abbreviation for pkg_resources.working_set.require()

above taken from:
https://pythonhosted.org/setuptools/pkg_resources.html#basic-workingset-methods

this fixes https://github.com/PyCQA/pylint/issues/780

Signed-off-by: Mateusz Bysiek <mb@mbdev.pl>
issues: [{u'raw': u'https://github.com/PyCQA/pylint/issues/780', u'refstyle': u'url', u'parts': [u'PyCQA', u'pylint', u'780', u'']}]

text:
Fix unpack_infer to fail if results are empty

This should prevent a StopIteration leaking when next is called
over unpack_infer.
raise_if_nothing_inferred is in bases, not in decorators.
